# Gitignored paths that `wt step copy-ignored` should copy into new
# worktrees. Whitelist — anything not listed here (tmp/, data/, coverage.out,
# build artefacts, .worktrees/ …) is left behind.
#
# The goal is a cold-start-free worktree: same secrets, same deps, no
# re-install, no re-download.

# Env + secrets — gitignored .env* needs to travel so a new worktree
# works out of the box (LLM_API_KEY etc.).
.env
.env.*
!.env.*.example

# Go vendored modules — if someone has vendored the module graph, copy it
# so `go build` doesn't re-download.
vendor/

# Node deps — tester UI (web/tester) may grow a node_modules in future;
# any nested one gets copied too.
node_modules/
